President Muhammadu Buhari, on Monday, attended the presidential campaign of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Bauchi state. Bola Tinubu, the party’s flag-bearer, and Kashim Shettima, his running mate, were at the rally held at the Abubakar Tafawa Balewa stadium in the state. Buhari presented the party’s flag to Tinubu and Sadique Abubakar, APC governorship candidate, for the state. Also present were Abdullahi Adamu, national chairman of the party; Simon Lalong, governor of Plateau; Ahmad Lawan, senate president, and Femi Gbajabiamila, speaker of the house of representatives. Below are photos.            